132
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:17,306
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He gave it to the Spencer restoration
two years ago

133
00:16:17,393 --> 00:16:19,304
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and you have done miracles here.

134
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:22,687
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We have done miracles here.
It's not all about me.

135
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,182
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you.

136
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:28,813
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These are new?

137
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:30,103
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Yeah.
- Great.

138
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:32,230
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If we get the cover of
Architectural Digest,

139
00:16:32,325 --> 00:16:34,907
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}we won't need to take
out another bank loan, will we?

140
00:16:38,748 --> 00:16:40,704
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know what your
daughter told me today?

141
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:41,864
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

142
00:16:42,585 --> 00:16:44,826
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She said your wife gave her to you.

143
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:51,083
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kids say all kinds of
things they don't mean.

144
00:16:54,931 --> 00:16:56,922
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It couldn't have gone any worse today.

145
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:01,051
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I feel like the evil stepmother.

146
00:17:01,729 --> 00:17:05,642
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The evil and very old stepmother.
Let's not forget the old part.

147
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:10,101
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because I was kind of thinking
you were looking a little ancient.

148
00:17:10,196 --> 00:17:11,606
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Oh, yeah?
- Oh, yeah.

149
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:13,445
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The stuffed bear? What was I thinking?

150
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:16,153
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on. It's great. She likes it.
I saw it in her room.

151
00:17:16,244 --> 00:17:17,575
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}On her bed?

152
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:20,703
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, above the bed. Hanging by a noose.

153
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:23,868
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's okay.
Nice sign of affection, I think.

154
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:20,971
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally. Her name is Sally.

155
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:46,697
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally!

156
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,222
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you think?

157
00:20:35,985 --> 00:20:37,316
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. Looks great.

158
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:41,483
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Have you seen Sally?
- Yeah, she's on the bench.

159
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:45,111
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally!

160
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:58,397
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It is not safe for you back here.

161
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,817
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey. What's going on? Everything okay?

162
00:22:01,904 --> 00:22:03,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep her out from the back of the house.

163
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:05,983
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She could fall in.
We'd be in a hell of a mess.

164
00:22:06,075 --> 00:22:07,861
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't do anything.

165
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:11,698
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's pits. Old wells.
It's dangerous for a child.

166
00:22:11,789 --> 00:22:14,781
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Harris is right, Sally. He knows.
His grandfather worked at the house.

167
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:16,831
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You shouldn't be back here.
- But I found a basement.

168
00:22:16,919 --> 00:22:18,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There is no basement.

169
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:20,377
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Easy, Harris. I'll take her. It's okay.

170
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:24,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's there! It's right there!

171
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:32,469
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's a reason
this house is called Fallen Mill.

172
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:35,176
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The English had a mill here,
and it fell into a sinkhole.

173
00:22:35,271 --> 00:22:37,762
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's why most of the houses around here
don't have basements.

174
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:39,017
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This one does.

175
00:22:39,108 --> 00:22:42,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You may want to check this out.
- It's unsafe for a child.

176
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,229
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pull on that.

177
00:22:45,072 --> 00:22:47,108
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look! I told you it was here!

178
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:48,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can you believe this?

179
00:22:55,457 --> 00:22:57,038
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is definitely hollow.

180
00:22:58,752 --> 00:23:00,083
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to get some tools.

181
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:07,542
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You sure you want to do this now?
- Of course! You kidding?

182
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:09,968
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We can fix this easy if we have to.

183
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:12,171
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You may want to step back.

184
00:23:16,145 --> 00:23:17,476
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Hurst, I...

185
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:36,662
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's a door in here.

186
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:42,788
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where did you put the old house keys?

187
00:23:42,880 --> 00:23:45,667
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're in your junk drawer in the office.

188
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:46,834
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay.

189
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:49,174
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Have a look.

190
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:20,364
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, wow.

191
00:24:21,043 --> 00:24:23,204
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You be careful, Sally. Okay?
- Okay.

192
00:24:26,215 --> 00:24:28,581
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How the hell did we miss this?

193
00:24:33,973 --> 00:24:35,634
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That must be the garden window.

194
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:48,313
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's all of his paints and old
color pencils. This is amazing.

195
00:25:04,253 --> 00:25:06,665
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wow. Alex, look at this.

196
00:25:15,097 --> 00:25:16,507
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Harris, did you know about this?

197
00:25:16,598 --> 00:25:20,466
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This place isn't safe. Especially for kids.

198
00:25:20,561 --> 00:25:22,051
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's okay. I'll keep an eye on her.

199
00:25:24,189 --> 00:25:26,100
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This must be where Blackwood worked.

200
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:27,397
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I found another door.

201
00:25:28,068 --> 00:25:30,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Look at these sketches.
- It's an ash pit, I think.

202
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:33,854
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. It's bolted shut.

203
00:25:34,533 --> 00:25:35,943
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These are incredible.

204
00:25:42,541 --> 00:25:44,122
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay. Let's go, Sally.

205
00:25:55,304 --> 00:25:56,635
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, Sally. Let's go.

206
00:25:57,973 --> 00:25:58,962
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, come on.

207
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:03,137
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This must be like King Tut's tomb for you.

208
00:26:03,312 --> 00:26:07,146
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Which is why we shouldn't be touching
anything. This stuff must be valuable.

209
00:26:07,316 --> 00:26:10,558
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- She's gone.
- No, she will come back.

210
00:26:10,736 --> 00:26:12,567
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They always do.

211
00:26:12,654 --> 00:26:15,111
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, they always do.

212
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:53,021
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't think that's important, Alan.

213
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:57,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, I just need to make sure I get
the paintings and furniture

214
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:59,614
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}back in time for the dinner.

215
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:01,199
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You told me you could.

216
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:04,494
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on.
How long have we known each other?

217
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:06,492
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll write you a post-dated check.

218
00:27:09,044 --> 00:27:10,454
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hold on.

219
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:15,961
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's either walnut or mahogany,
I think. Yeah.

220
00:27:16,969 --> 00:27:20,962
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There you are.
I thought maybe we could bake scones.

221
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:25,307
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I promised Mrs. Underhill
we wouldn't make too much of a mess.

222
00:27:25,394 --> 00:27:26,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. That's all right.

223
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:30,641
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What have you got there?

224
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:34,729
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My doll. And my drawing stuff.

225
00:27:41,577 --> 00:27:44,535
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Looks like it's just you and I
baking scones today.

226
00:27:51,795 --> 00:27:53,911
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I made sandwiches for everyone.

227
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:40,548
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, open the grate.

228
00:28:40,636 --> 00:28:44,128
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, open the grate. Set us free.

229
00:28:50,312 --> 00:28:51,643
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who are you?

230
00:28:52,940 --> 00:28:54,271
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you look like?

231
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:57,808
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We've been locked up for so long.

232
00:28:57,903 --> 00:28:59,439
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Set us free.

233
00:29:03,659 --> 00:29:06,947
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come down.
You'll see what it's like down here.

234
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:08,618
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wait a minute, will ya?

235
00:29:08,747 --> 00:29:12,080
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's other children down here.
They're just like you.

236
00:29:12,167 --> 00:29:14,374
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come and play with them.

237
00:29:15,254 --> 00:29:16,494
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally?

238
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:22,165
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally.

239
00:29:24,346 --> 00:29:25,961
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you doing down here?

240
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:31,092
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I heard something.
- Rats, probably. It's time for dinner.

241
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:34,102
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- It was a voice.
- Really smart rats, then.

242
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:35,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! Listen.

243
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:54,539
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nothing. Come on. Let's go, kiddo.

244
00:30:09,224 --> 00:30:11,806
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I forgot my bag.
- Hurry it up, then.

245
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,053
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, now!

246
00:32:08,260 --> 00:32:10,751
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We can get this tomorrow. We can't
get the rest of these for two weeks.

247
00:32:10,846 --> 00:32:12,461
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What about the burnt umber?

248
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:15,847
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's much warmer,
and we can get it for half the price.

249
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:18,551
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You not hungry? Sally?

250
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:22,771
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you like rice?

251
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:26,979
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mrs. Underhill made apple pie for dessert.

252
00:32:27,195 --> 00:32:30,528
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Apple pie has gluten, and Mommy says
gluten is bad for my concentration.

253
00:32:30,615 --> 00:32:32,651
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, come on. You love apple pie.

254
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:35,358
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We can worry
about your concentration tomorrow.

255
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:37,194
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mommy says no gluten.

256
00:32:37,789 --> 00:32:39,199
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's your mother filling your head with?

257
00:32:39,291 --> 00:32:40,781
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- How about some chocolate milk?
- No.

258
00:32:40,876 --> 00:32:42,286
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I'll make something else.
- Hold on.

259
00:32:42,377 --> 00:32:45,289
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, you need to eat this,
or you can go to your room. Okay?

260
00:32:47,048 --> 00:32:48,834
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good night, Dad.

261
00:32:56,183 --> 00:32:57,263
