393
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:33,404
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He asked me to leave the cellar.

394
00:46:33,582 --> 00:46:35,664
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was so dark in there,
he must have stumbled.

395
00:46:35,751 --> 00:46:37,616
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Mr. Hurst, thank God!
- What happened?

396
00:46:37,712 --> 00:46:39,543
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Are you William Harris' employer?
- Yeah.

397
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:40,870
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's been an accident.

398
00:46:41,132 --> 00:46:45,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Are you okay? Where's Sally?
- I'm sorry. She saw him.

399
00:46:45,177 --> 00:46:47,213
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I tried to cover her eyes,
and I was too late.

400
00:46:47,305 --> 00:46:48,966
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Where is she?
- She's in the garden.

401
00:46:49,140 --> 00:46:50,471
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I am sorry!

402
00:46:53,060 --> 00:46:54,470
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally?

403
00:47:13,414 --> 00:47:14,574
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hi.

404
00:47:17,668 --> 00:47:18,999
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you scared?

405
00:47:22,423 --> 00:47:23,754
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you want to talk about it?

406
00:47:26,844 --> 00:47:28,835
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Is Mr. Harris going to die?

407
00:47:30,848 --> 00:47:32,008
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, Sally.

408
00:47:33,184 --> 00:47:34,845
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He is going to be okay.

409
00:47:48,115 --> 00:47:49,651
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can I show you something?

410
00:48:23,067 --> 00:48:25,479
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is my favorite part of the house.

411
00:48:25,653 --> 00:48:27,234
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blackwood loved nature.

412
00:48:28,447 --> 00:48:32,031
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He imported these fish from Japan.
And so did we.

413
00:48:33,661 --> 00:48:34,992
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're called koi.

414
00:48:36,247 --> 00:48:37,987
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're considered magical.

415
00:48:38,958 --> 00:48:41,950
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Badgers can spot them
against the mud at the bottom

416
00:48:42,128 --> 00:48:43,538
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}because of their bright colors.

417
00:48:44,630 --> 00:48:50,591
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So what makes them special
is also what makes them vulnerable.

418
00:48:51,554 --> 00:48:53,135
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They have to be tough.

419
00:48:54,974 --> 00:48:56,464
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you, too, Sally.

420
00:49:01,147 --> 00:49:03,012
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't touch your clothes.

421
00:49:06,026 --> 00:49:08,267
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I swear to God, I never touched them!

422
00:49:10,573 --> 00:49:12,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I didn't touch them.
- Sally.

423
00:49:12,867 --> 00:49:16,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't! Didn't cut them, I promise.

424
00:49:16,871 --> 00:49:19,112
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't care about my clothes.

425
00:49:24,712 --> 00:49:27,124
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I can't really tell. 1804, I think.

426
00:49:27,965 --> 00:49:30,627
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's hard to see.
The coin is pretty worn down.

427
00:49:35,222 --> 00:49:37,383
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She probably found it
in Blackwood's studio.

428
00:49:38,225 --> 00:49:40,637
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't want her
going down there anymore.

429
00:49:40,728 --> 00:49:43,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm worried about her, Kim. It's not safe.

430
00:49:54,325 --> 00:49:56,031
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- This is Joanne.
- Mommy?

431
00:49:56,202 --> 00:49:58,864
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, sweetie, it's you! How are you?

432
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:00,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can I come home?

433
00:50:01,165 --> 00:50:04,157
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You want to come...
The sashimi. Stuart, the sashimi.

434
00:50:04,251 --> 00:50:06,492
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I don't like it here.
- You what?

435
00:50:06,670 --> 00:50:11,505
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Honey, don't fret. It's so beautiful there.
You just need to get used to it.

436
00:50:11,592 --> 00:50:13,173
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But it's cold.

437
00:50:13,344 --> 00:50:15,585
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Honey, what?
- My bed is too big.

438
00:50:15,763 --> 00:50:17,845
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Sweetheart.
- And I think I'm getting sick.

439
00:50:17,932 --> 00:50:19,638
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not getting sick.

440
00:50:19,725 --> 00:50:24,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It will take a little tiny bit of getting used to,
but you are going to be so happy there.

441
00:50:24,647 --> 00:50:27,684
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay? I promise. You'll get used to it.

442
00:50:29,068 --> 00:50:31,104
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I got to go, honey. Mommy's got to go.

443
00:50:31,278 --> 00:50:33,769
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll see you soon. Bye!

444
00:51:30,671 --> 00:51:31,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim?

445
00:51:41,473 --> 00:51:43,464
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Don't leave.
- What's wrong?

446
00:51:45,019 --> 00:51:46,680
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Even when I'm asleep.

447
00:51:50,024 --> 00:51:51,560
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And don't turn off the lights.

448
00:51:54,528 --> 00:51:55,859
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll be right here.

449
00:51:58,240 --> 00:51:59,355
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on.

450
00:53:23,951 --> 00:53:24,986
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim?

451
00:53:36,797 --> 00:53:39,163
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I love you. I love you.

452
00:54:37,316 --> 00:54:39,898
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Daddy! Daddy!

453
00:54:40,736 --> 00:54:42,192
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Daddy, please!

454
00:54:42,863 --> 00:54:43,852
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Daddy!

455
00:54:45,491 --> 00:54:47,573
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, what's the matter?

456
00:54:54,374 --> 00:54:56,535
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't want them to come anymore.

457
00:54:56,627 --> 00:54:57,616
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who, Sally?

458
00:54:58,504 --> 00:54:59,619
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The little things.

459
00:55:01,006 --> 00:55:03,543
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They live in the basement.
They gave me the silver dollar.

460
00:55:04,593 --> 00:55:09,428
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They said they wanted to be my friend.
But they're horrible and mean.

461
00:55:12,226 --> 00:55:14,888
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You just had a nightmare.
- Don't say that!

462
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:16,677
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's okay.

463
00:55:18,899 --> 00:55:20,059
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My bear.

464
00:55:21,276 --> 00:55:23,107
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look what they did to my bear.

465
00:55:53,934 --> 00:55:58,394
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your dad tells me art is your
favorite subject. I wish I could draw.

466
00:55:59,314 --> 00:56:00,929
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Drawing is easy.

467
00:56:02,609 --> 00:56:04,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The other kids can't do feet and hands.

468
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:09,359
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When you say "the other kids,"
do you feel they're different from you?

469
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:11,155
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My doctor back home asked me that.

470
00:56:11,243 --> 00:56:12,949
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What was your answer?

471
00:56:16,456 --> 00:56:20,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay. Let's start with something easier.

472
00:56:21,420 --> 00:56:22,956
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's your favorite color?

473
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:26,129
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What is that? Purple?

474
00:56:26,800 --> 00:56:27,789
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Black.

475
00:56:29,636 --> 00:56:33,595
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about these little things you saw?
What do you think they are?

476
00:56:40,731 --> 00:56:42,062
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Fairies.

477
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:45,015
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Or gnomes.

478
00:56:45,193 --> 00:56:46,353
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But scary ones?

479
00:56:49,615 --> 00:56:51,321
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you say they know your name?

480
00:56:57,164 --> 00:56:58,324
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They talk to you?

481
00:56:59,708 --> 00:57:00,697
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes.

482
00:57:04,504 --> 00:57:05,835
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do they say?

483
00:57:07,674 --> 00:57:09,164
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They want to play with me.

484
00:57:09,718 --> 00:57:11,049
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Is that all?

485
00:57:15,974 --> 00:57:18,010
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They say my parents don't love me.

486
00:57:22,022 --> 00:57:23,558
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can I go now?

487
00:57:23,732 --> 00:57:25,563
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just a few more questions, okay?

488
00:57:44,044 --> 00:57:49,164
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There is a lot of anxiety in that little girl
and a deep belief that she's not wanted.

489
00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:52,883
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I believe that's what's triggering
these fantastic episodes.

490
00:57:53,095 --> 00:57:56,883
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She told me she found a little tray filled
with teeth right inside that fireplace.

491
00:57:57,057 --> 00:58:00,424
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. She found a tooth,
but that doesn't mean anything, does it?

492
00:58:00,727 --> 00:58:05,721
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's constructing this elaborate fantasy
about wrinkles, claws, fangs.

493
00:58:05,816 --> 00:58:08,398
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's individuated
each one of those things,

494
00:58:08,568 --> 00:58:10,399
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}her imaginary world, its inhabitants.

495
00:58:10,487 --> 00:58:13,320
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's as detailed as any
I've ever encountered.

496
00:58:14,282 --> 00:58:15,613
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do we do?

497
00:58:15,742 --> 00:58:18,028
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'd like to try her on a
stronger medication, for a start.

498
00:58:18,120 --> 00:58:20,327
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll ask her doctor in LA to send me a copy
of her charts.

499
00:58:20,414 --> 00:58:22,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You call my office,
make another appointment.

500
00:58:22,457 --> 00:58:23,446
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay, great.

501
00:58:23,542 --> 00:58:25,749
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Meanwhile, I'll give you something
to help her sleep.

502
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:35,342
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to be late. I can't believe it.

503
00:58:35,429 --> 00:58:38,296
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If we don't get the extension on this loan,
we're not going to get the paintings

504
00:58:38,390 --> 00:58:40,255
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}or the furniture back on time.

505
00:58:41,518 --> 00:58:43,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We forgot the invitations
for the historical society.

506
00:58:43,812 --> 00:58:47,179
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe we should just
postpone the dinner.

507
00:58:47,441 --> 00:58:50,729
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim, it's Architectural Digest.
We have to get the house on the cover.

508
00:58:50,819 --> 00:58:51,899
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I know.
- If we don't,

509
00:58:51,987 --> 00:58:54,694
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm never going to get my career back,
and we're not going to sell the place.

510
00:58:54,781 --> 00:58:57,193
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- How often have we talked about this?
- What about what's been happening?

511
00:58:57,284 --> 00:58:58,524
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Harris? That was an accident.

512
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:01,701
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I'm talking about Sally.
- It's all in her head!

513
00:59:01,788 --> 00:59:04,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's real to her.
It doesn't matter if we see it.

514
00:59:04,791 --> 00:59:06,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Come on!
- Calm down!

515
00:59:08,336 --> 00:59:11,499
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to walk. It'll be faster.
I'll see you back at home.

516
00:59:35,363 --> 00:59:39,652
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not sure how lucid he'll be.
He's pretty heavily sedated.

517
01:00:11,858 --> 01:00:14,691
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Harris, I know this is difficult,

518
01:00:15,362 --> 01:00:17,694
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but I need to understand something.

519
01:00:18,365 --> 01:00:21,323
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I need to know what Sally saw
so that I can help her.

520
01:00:22,869 --> 01:00:26,862
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Is she out of the house?

521
01:00:27,749 --> 01:00:28,738
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No.

522
01:00:31,253 --> 01:00:32,368
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Out.

523
01:00:33,255 --> 01:00:36,372
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She needs to be out of there.

524
01:00:38,718 --> 01:00:39,753
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why?

525
01:00:43,723 --> 01:00:45,714
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why was that room sealed up?

526
01:00:49,229 --> 01:00:51,515
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Grandfather.

527
01:00:51,606 --> 01:00:54,723
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your grandfather closed it up?

528
01:00:55,026 --> 01:00:56,562
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Yes.
- Why?

529
01:00:58,613 --> 01:00:59,728
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After...

530
01:01:01,741 --> 01:01:02,730
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After...

531
01:01:06,454 --> 01:01:07,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After what?

532
01:01:09,833 --> 01:01:10,913
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blackwood.

533
01:01:13,461 --> 01:01:14,871
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What about Blackwood?

534
01:01:17,424 --> 01:01:22,259
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lot 1134.

535
01:01:23,430 --> 01:01:25,261
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Public library.

536
01:01:27,225 --> 01:01:31,559
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Get her out of the house.

537
01:02:00,133 --> 01:02:03,466
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The library will be closing in 15 minutes.

538
01:02:03,637 --> 01:02:07,971
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The library will be closing in 15 minutes.
Thank you.

539
01:02:09,851 --> 01:02:10,931
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excuse me.

540
01:02:12,687 --> 01:02:14,894
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Can I help you?
- I'm looking for the librarian.

541
01:02:17,776 --> 01:02:18,811
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lot 1134.

542
01:02:21,154 --> 01:02:23,987
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Emerson Blackwood, Special Collections.
One sec.

543
01:02:29,913 --> 01:02:31,244
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Right this way.

544
01:02:50,350 --> 01:02:53,433
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can't remember the last time
anyone requested these. They're beautiful.

545
01:02:53,520 --> 01:02:55,977
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm a designer.
I've been working at Fallen Mill.

546
01:02:56,064 --> 01:02:58,521
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wow. Now, that's a privilege.

547
01:02:59,234 --> 01:03:02,567
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Personally, I think Emerson Blackwood
rivaled Audubon.

548
01:03:04,030 --> 01:03:05,361
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come across his mural?

549
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:07,689
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A mural? Where?

550
01:03:07,784 --> 01:03:11,276
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There in the house, supposedly.
If you do, I'd love to see it.

551
01:03:46,865 --> 01:03:47,854
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello?

552
01:04:07,469 --> 01:04:11,178
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, it's pretty ironic, really.

553
01:04:11,264 --> 01:04:15,974
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For a committed realist, someone who
insisted on drawing only from nature,

554
01:04:16,311 --> 01:04:18,302
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to do these at the end of his life.

555
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:21,354
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've looked at everything by Blackwood,
and I've never seen any of these.

556
01:04:21,441 --> 01:04:24,183
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You wouldn't.
The family made it a restricted donation.

557
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:26,984
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- These may never be published.
- Is it possible to get copies?

558
01:04:28,531 --> 01:04:30,442
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll see what I can do.

559
01:04:30,658 --> 01:04:33,070
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Wrinkles, claws, teeth?"

560
01:04:33,953 --> 01:04:35,659
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Have you ever read Machen?

561
01:04:35,955 --> 01:04:37,786
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Arthur Machen. Welsh.

562
01:04:38,249 --> 01:04:39,955
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He believed in fairy folk,

563
01:04:40,043 --> 01:04:44,161
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}these ancient entities
from the netherworld, predating mankind.

564
01:04:44,422 --> 01:04:48,506
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blackwood quotes him extensively.
Here, that line. There.

565
01:04:48,802 --> 01:04:50,633
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"One life must be taken."

566
01:04:50,804 --> 01:04:54,171
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These creatures had to take one human life
every time they emerged.

567
01:04:54,265 --> 01:04:55,505
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to replenish their ranks.

568
01:04:55,600 --> 01:04:59,889
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Many of these creatures fed on the bones,
the teeth of young children.

569
01:05:00,271 --> 01:05:03,308
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And then there's a truce, a pact of sorts,

570
01:05:03,400 --> 01:05:05,561
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}between Pope Sylvester II
and these ancient beings

571
01:05:05,652 --> 01:05:07,483
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}in the year 999.

572
01:05:08,321 --> 01:05:12,985
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}In exchange for human teeth, they start
leaving silver pieces under the pillow.

573
01:05:19,833 --> 01:05:23,997
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, this is the last known drawing
by Emerson Blackwood,

574
01:05:24,754 --> 01:05:28,667
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}made shortly before his disappearance
and the loss of his child.

575
01:05:29,384 --> 01:05:30,590
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}His child?

576
01:05:30,885 --> 01:05:33,922
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blackwood's only son vanished, lost.

577
01:05:34,013 --> 01:05:37,722
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not long after, Blackwood himself
disappeared without a trace.

578
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:03,197
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No!

579
01:06:36,534 --> 01:06:40,447
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! No! Please!

580
01:06:55,720 --> 01:06:57,005
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No!

581
01:07:12,612 --> 01:07:14,102
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, what's wrong?

582
01:07:15,073 --> 01:07:16,904
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, open the door!

583
01:07:27,126 --> 01:07:28,457
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my God!

584
01:07:41,391 --> 01:07:43,598
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Dear, thank goodness you're home.

585
01:07:43,768 --> 01:07:46,134
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Where is she?
- I put her to bed.

586
01:07:46,312 --> 01:07:48,052
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She wouldn't stop screaming.

587
01:07:59,826 --> 01:08:00,986
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally?

588
01:08:43,411 --> 01:08:44,491
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim!

589
01:08:45,580 --> 01:08:46,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's not down here.

590
01:08:46,914 --> 01:08:49,405
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think she's run away.
She's done it before.

591
01:08:51,961 --> 01:08:55,749
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Once she tried to walk all the way back
to LA from our family home in Boston.

592
01:08:55,840 --> 01:08:59,082
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I wouldn't be surprised
if that's what she's doing.

593
01:09:08,895 --> 01:09:10,886
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I went and visited Harris today.

594
01:09:12,607 --> 01:09:14,893
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blackwood had a son. Did you know that?

595
01:09:14,984 --> 01:09:17,225
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And when he was eight, he disappeared.

596
01:09:17,320 --> 01:09:19,185
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And Blackwood vanished a few days later.

597
01:09:19,280 --> 01:09:21,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why are you telling me this?

598
01:09:21,115 --> 01:09:23,197
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A lot of what Blackwood wrote
at the end of his life,

599
01:09:23,284 --> 01:09:27,277
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it's awfully close to Sally's story,
gnomes, creatures, all of it.

600
01:09:27,372 --> 01:09:28,782
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim, don't tell me you believe this.

601
01:09:28,873 --> 01:09:30,989
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Something terrible happened
in that basement.

602
01:09:31,542 --> 01:09:33,328
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- We need to leave.
- What are you talking about?

603
01:09:33,419 --> 01:09:35,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Put a million miles
between us and that house.

604
01:09:35,421 --> 01:09:39,005
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Every cent I have is in that house.
And you're saying that we just walk away?

605
01:09:39,092 --> 01:09:42,175
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I accept that
my daughter has problems, okay?

606
01:09:42,261 --> 01:09:44,126
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you. We all know that.

607
01:09:44,222 --> 01:09:46,508
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But they do not involve
monsters in the basement.

608
01:09:47,642 --> 01:09:48,973
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There she is.

609
01:10:04,117 --> 01:10:06,449
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, Sally. Get in the car.

610
01:10:10,289 --> 01:10:14,282
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, please, just tonight,
and after the party we'll talk, okay?

611
01:10:38,985 --> 01:10:44,321
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Four, three, two and one.

612
01:10:45,992 --> 01:10:46,981
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There.

613
01:10:49,036 --> 01:10:51,823
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After the party, I will get you out of here.

614
01:10:51,998 --> 01:10:53,659
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No matter what. I promise.

615
01:11:00,381 --> 01:11:02,167
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Sally!
- No.

616
01:11:02,341 --> 01:11:03,626
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I took it from them.

617
01:11:03,885 --> 01:11:06,376
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You can't have this.
- They stole it. You don't understand.

618
01:11:06,471 --> 01:11:08,712
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I need it to fight back.
- Absolutely not.

619
01:11:08,806 --> 01:11:09,841
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please!

620
01:11:12,560 --> 01:11:14,221
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nobody believes me.

621
01:11:16,814 --> 01:11:18,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sally, I trust you,

622
01:11:19,901 --> 01:11:23,064
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and you can tell me anything at all.

623
01:11:28,493 --> 01:11:33,823
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They don't like bright lights.Those things.

624
01:11:34,540 --> 01:11:35,529
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They don't?

625
01:11:40,588 --> 01:11:41,919
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then I have a good idea.

626
01:11:47,929 --> 01:11:49,635
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Jacoby, I am so
glad you could make it.

627
01:11:49,722 --> 01:11:51,587
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Alex, call me Charles.
- Charles.

628
01:11:51,682 --> 01:11:53,172
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- My wife, Evelyn.
- Hello, Alex.

629
01:11:53,267 --> 01:11:54,803
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's a pleasure. Come on in.

630
01:11:54,977 --> 01:11:58,515
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The house looks absolutely fantastic.

631
01:11:58,689 --> 01:12:00,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You've done a remarkable job.

632
01:12:00,191 --> 01:12:02,398
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, thank you.

633
01:12:02,568 --> 01:12:05,605
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- We'd love the nickel tour.
- Of course. That's the whole point.

634
01:12:05,780 --> 01:12:07,190
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The foyer, obviously.

635
01:12:07,365 --> 01:12:09,780
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The mahogany, we shipped from
the very same vendor

636
01:12:09,784 --> 01:12:13,572
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}that Blackwood used in London.
It's been in business since 1865.

637
01:12:13,663 --> 01:12:16,496
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know Bill from the heritage board.

638
01:12:16,666 --> 01:12:19,453
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Easy, Sally. Not everybody
wants to have their photograph taken.

639
01:12:36,602 --> 01:12:38,092
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, Alex, where's Kim?

640
01:12:38,271 --> 01:12:39,602
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think she's still upstairs.

641
01:12:39,689 --> 01:12:43,682
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why don't you step into the library,
grab a drink, and I'll join you in a moment.

642
01:13:09,677 --> 01:13:11,884
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim, hey, what's going on?

643
01:13:12,805 --> 01:13:15,387
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Her drawings.
They're exactly Blackwood's sketches.

644
01:13:16,058 --> 01:13:18,800
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah, I'm sure she probably saw
your photographs and copied them.

645
01:13:18,895 --> 01:13:20,476
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, she didn't.

646
01:13:20,563 --> 01:13:22,645
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kim, please, Jacoby's here.

647
01:13:22,815 --> 01:13:25,978
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Alex, this is your daughter!
- I know.

648
01:13:26,152 --> 01:13:28,143
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is serious!

649
01:13:28,321 --> 01:13:30,864
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just because you keep denying it
does not mean

650
01:13:30,865 --> 01:13:32,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- it's not happening.
